### StreamableClientTransport Configuration

Source: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/%40v0.3.1/mcp

StreamableClientTransport facilitates communication with an MCP endpoint that supports the streamable HTTP transport. It includes configurations for the endpoint URL, HTTP client, and retry attempts for reconnections.

```go
type StreamableClientTransport struct {
	Endpoint   string
	HTTPClient *http.Client
	// MaxRetries is the maximum number of times to attempt a reconnect before giving up.
	// It defaults to 5. To disable retries, use a negative number.
	MaxRetries int
}

// A StreamableClientTransport is a Transport that can communicate with an MCP endpoint serving the streamable HTTP transport defined by the 2025-03-26 version of the spec.
```

