### Define a Tool in Go

Source: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/%40v1.2.0-pre.1/mcp

The Tool struct defines a callable tool, including its metadata, description, input/output schemas, and display name. It supports optional annotations for richer descriptions and icons for visual representation. The InputSchema and OutputSchema fields accept any type that can be JSON-marshaled into a valid JSON schema.

```go
type Tool struct {
	Meta `json:"_meta,omitempty"`
	Annotations *ToolAnnotations `json:"annotations,omitempty"`
	Description string `json:"description,omitempty"`
	InputSchema any `json:"inputSchema"`
	Name string `json:"name"`
	OutputSchema any `json:"outputSchema,omitempty"`
	Title string `json:"title,omitempty"`
	Icons []Icon `json:"icons,omitempty"`
}
```

