Source: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/%40v1.1.0-pre.1/mcp

The Tool structure defines a tool that a client can call. It includes metadata, optional annotations, a description, input and output schemas, and display names. The input and output schemas must conform to JSON Schema drafts supported by the SDK.

```go
type Tool struct {
	Meta `json:"_meta,omitempty"`
	Annotations *ToolAnnotations `json:"annotations,omitempty"`
	Description string `json:"description,omitempty"`
	InputSchema any `json:"inputSchema"`
	Name string `json:"name"`
	OutputSchema any `json:"outputSchema,omitempty"`
	Title string `json:"title,omitempty"`
}

```

